The evidence with the title 'Transcript: Obama's speech against the Iraq War : NPR ' says Jan 20, 2009  ... Barack Obama delivered in Chicago on oct. 2, 2002. In his speech, Obama said that what he was opposed to was "a dumb war  ... A rash war." He said the war was a "cynical attempt" to shove "ideological agendas down our throats" and would distract from domestic problems such as poverty and health ... 
